22
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:41,210
Doesn't look like you lost someone
You are the one who seems lost!

23
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:45,077
- Someone must be searching for you
- I want Nila

24
00:05:45,167 --> 00:05:47,613
This is a police station
You shouldn't be here

25
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:50,909
Come with a friend, relative or a lawyer

26
00:05:53,367 --> 00:05:55,108
You'll find a lawyer in court

27
00:06:01,267 --> 00:06:03,440
It's time to go to the court
Shall we leave?

28
00:06:03,533 --> 00:06:08,278
Make sure everyone boards the van

29
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:26,371
Rape or drugs? Tell me what case

30
00:06:26,467 --> 00:06:27,445
We'll take you out in a jiffy

31
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:29,274
Go in like this
Out in a jiffy like that

32
00:06:29,367 --> 00:06:31,608
Go in...get out
We'll take you out in a jiffy

33
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,646
What are we here for?

34
00:06:35,733 --> 00:06:38,680
Hey! You there!

35
00:06:39,867 --> 00:06:41,278
How did you get in here?

36
00:06:44,033 --> 00:06:44,943
Get down

37
00:06:46,967 --> 00:06:48,275
This one is without a lawyer!

38
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:52,874
Go in like this
Out in a jiffy like that

39
00:06:52,967 --> 00:06:54,446
- What's your case?
- Murder

40
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:57,103
- How many?
- One

41
00:06:57,467 --> 00:07:00,846
Just 1? I expected much more from you

42
00:07:00,933 --> 00:07:04,676
- Whom did you kill?
- Lawyer who defended me and lost

43
00:07:06,567 --> 00:07:08,069
You are my lawyer from now on

44
00:07:08,167 --> 00:07:12,172
I am not a lawyer
I'm a tea shop owner

45
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:13,643
How come you are dressed this way?

46
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:16,104
Because it's so cold, sir

47
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:24,005
You have even started
selling tea and coffee, sir?

48
00:07:24,133 --> 00:07:27,080
- Looks like that will be my job!
- How can you say that, 'Mr Lawyer'?

49
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:30,280
- What did you call me?
- 'Mr Lawyer'

50
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:33,275
Looks like I myself need to be reminded

51
00:07:33,733 --> 00:07:35,144
Why don't you get me a case?

52
00:07:35,233 --> 00:07:39,978
Look at that man over there in a sweater
Catch hold of him

53
00:07:40,067 --> 00:07:41,171
Good one?

54
00:07:47,233 --> 00:07:49,270
My boss is a very experienced lawyer

55
00:07:49,367 --> 00:07:51,608
You can go in like this
Be out in a jiffy like that

56
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:52,974
You don't worry about it

57
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:11,010
Stop!

58
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,443
Grab him, sir

59
00:08:17,533 --> 00:08:21,709
He claims he will kill a lawyer
Kaatumiraandi! Senseless savage!!

60
00:08:22,133 --> 00:08:23,942
Dented tin-head!!

61
00:08:32,267 --> 00:08:35,043
Many a miss between
the mouth and the magistrate!

62
00:08:42,933 --> 00:08:44,276
Don't you worry, sir

63
00:08:44,367 --> 00:08:46,870
Come in

64
00:08:46,967 --> 00:08:48,947
Please be seated

65
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:04,277
I've got hold of a super client
Come to our room immediately

66
00:09:04,533 --> 00:09:07,104
I'm inside the court room
Call me later

67
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:10,579
it's not as if you are defending a case
You are just gaping at the proceedings

68
00:09:10,667 --> 00:09:11,941
Come out

69
00:09:21,033 --> 00:09:24,606
I never thought
I'll get back my property so soon

70
00:09:25,467 --> 00:09:28,277
- Anu, how long?
- I'm coming

71
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:33,706
I only wanted
what's my rightful inheritance

72
00:09:34,067 --> 00:09:36,638
You blatantly lied
that I am not my dad's son!

73
00:09:36,733 --> 00:09:40,271
If you had come to me first
I'd have said the same about him

74
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,838
I'll take care

75
00:09:50,033 --> 00:09:52,274
How many times
to tell you not to call me 'dear'?

76
00:09:52,433 --> 00:09:54,777
Why are you irritated?
You haven't got a case till now?

77
00:09:56,633 --> 00:09:58,442
Mind you r business!

78
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:06,844
It's some missing case

79
00:10:06,967 --> 00:10:10,779
Imagine! He must be filthy rich to
roam around Chennai wearing a sweater!!

80
00:10:10,867 --> 00:10:13,473
He must forever be used
to air conditioning

81
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:26,646
I'll call you discreetly from inside
Let's pretend to be in great demand

82
00:10:28,933 --> 00:10:33,382
We are dependent on him this month
Don't mess it up as usual

83
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:55,207
That's my business card for you

84
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,970
How can I help you?

85
00:11:14,733 --> 00:11:18,146
Who are you?
Where did you come from?

86
00:11:18,233 --> 00:11:20,338
Krishna

87
00:11:25,933 --> 00:11:28,675
Goats...cows

88
00:11:28,767 --> 00:11:30,371
Not cows

89
00:11:33,733 --> 00:11:36,475
Lots of trees

90
00:11:36,933 --> 00:11:38,674
There's a huge tree

91
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:42,476
There's major feud
between the Ambani brothers

92
00:11:42,567 --> 00:11:45,810
They want you to fly to Delhi tonight

93
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:49,881
I'll tell them you won't come
without completing this case

94
00:11:54,167 --> 00:11:56,738
You were saying...

95
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:09,476
Gate...goats...cows

96
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,636
There's a huge tree

97
00:12:14,167 --> 00:12:21,710
Your client is waiting out with
Rs 150000 for winning his case

98
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:25,310
I'm so sorry I blurted
your fees in front of our client

99
00:12:30,233 --> 00:12:31,644
You continue...

100
00:12:33,467 --> 00:12:36,539
That huge tree

101
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:40,579
Is he still at that same tree?!

102
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:48,147
I put chocolates into a bag...tie it...

103
00:12:57,767 --> 00:13:02,307
Goats and cows lying down by the roadside

104
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:07,140
I'll be right back

105
00:13:12,267 --> 00:13:14,338
What are you up to?

106
00:13:17,333 --> 00:13:18,437
Urgent case

107
00:13:18,533 --> 00:13:20,479
She needs to get divorced
She's getting married this evening

108
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,136
You got to help her right now

109
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:34,813
Listen to me

110
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:37,810
Nila (moon) will be seen tonight
We'll hold it safely for you

111
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:40,471
You come back tonight

112
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,480
You couldn't have found a better case!

113
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:51,804
How did I know he'd be a nut case?

114
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:56,313
Go and get a good case

115
00:13:57,500 --> 00:14:00,674
Serves me right for not studying well!

116
00:14:09,567 --> 00:14:11,308
Why is he still here?

117
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:15,405
You ask me to bring in a case for you
Then you ask me to pack him off

118
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,275
What do you take me for?
'Use and throw'?

119
00:14:17,367 --> 00:14:20,143
Fine...how do we go out now?

120
00:14:23,633 --> 00:14:26,512
Drink this tea
I have ordered lunch

121
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:29,672
Usually we try to get our client out

122
00:14:29,767 --> 00:14:34,011
Now, we are breaking our heads
how to get ourselves out!

123
00:14:38,967 --> 00:14:40,913
What's this new case I'm unaware of

124
00:14:47,567 --> 00:14:48,545
That's a political recommendation

125
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:04,979
You blabbered to that man
you won't grant him divorce!

126
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:34,776
What are you glaring at me for?

127
00:15:34,867 --> 00:15:38,440
Pig faced bum...grab him
He threatens to kill lawyers

128
00:15:38,533 --> 00:15:41,377
Kaatumiraandi! Barbaric beast!!
Put him behind bars

129
00:15:41,467 --> 00:15:46,007
We can't, sir
He is out on bail

130
00:15:51,967 --> 00:15:53,275
If you are free you can visit my shop

131
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:56,007
Grab a bite and a cup of tea or coffee

132
00:16:03,867 --> 00:16:06,006
Let's run this way
Mr Sweater is there

133
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:10,505
This nutcase

134
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:13,177
How many times to tell you?!!!

135
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:22,109
He had Anu's card
I found him for you

136
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:26,580
This place is swarming with maniacs!

137
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:30,345
Get lost

138
00:16:34,467 --> 00:16:36,708
You want Nila?

139
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:41,009
We'll go bring it for you
You be here

140
00:16:42,567 --> 00:16:44,171
Don't follow us

141
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,743
We'll be back soon

142
00:16:51,133 --> 00:16:53,704
Just wait for us here

143
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,238
Moon...moon

144
00:17:10,267 --> 00:17:15,046
When, where, whom
we meet can be pre determined

145
00:18:10,267 --> 00:18:11,712
Are you Anu?

146
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:15,035
Court closes at 6:00 P.M

147
00:18:15,133 --> 00:18:19,172
We asked him to leave
We even beat him to a pulp

148
00:18:19,267 --> 00:18:20,712
He's refusing to budge from here

149
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:24,570
We found your business card on him
Do you know him?

150
00:18:25,100 --> 00:18:29,708
You promised...to bring Nila...for me

151
00:18:32,267 --> 00:18:36,044
It seems he is Krishna
He is mentally challenged

152
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:40,041
Avalanchi is a small village near Ooty

153
00:18:40,233 --> 00:18:44,545
I found out a Mr Victor
owns Emerald chocolate factory

154
00:18:44,633 --> 00:18:49,082
He's the only person to know
Krishna 's story fully

155
00:18:52,033 --> 00:18:57,346
They took Nila away

156
00:18:57,433 --> 00:19:00,744
I want my Nila

157
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,210
Please wait out...

158
00:19:02,300 --> 00:19:05,110
if he gets too emotional
his blood pressure will rise

159
00:19:17,633 --> 00:19:19,306
Who is Nila?

160
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:25,204
Is Nila his wife?

161
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,507
Or his sister?

162
00:19:32,233 --> 00:19:33,610
Who is Nila?

163
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:26,713
Hey look there! What's Krishna up to?

164
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:36,546
Get down

165
00:20:47,167 --> 00:20:50,876
You should be in your home
You shouldn't be down

166
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:53,206
You are such a tiny baby

167
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,877
Why are you so happy?

168
00:21:35,267 --> 00:21:40,876
I'll soon have a baby of my own
A mini girl or boy

169
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:46,508
She or he will ask me
to buy many a cuddly toy

170
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:50,446
From today I'll dance and rejoice

171
00:21:50,533 --> 00:21:54,208
...in absolute joy!

172
00:22:06,433 --> 00:22:11,974
I'll soon have a baby of my own
A mini girl or boy

173
00:22:12,067 --> 00:22:17,574
She or he will ask me
to buy many a cuddly toy

174
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:21,510
From today I'll dance and rejoice

175
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:24,877
...in absolute joy!

176
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:31,810
It will take an hour for me
to reach Cunnoor

177
00:22:31,900 --> 00:22:35,541
How slow can you be...no fear at all

178
00:22:35,633 --> 00:22:39,376
Relax! Don 't be angry
Krishna isn't here...that's wh y

179
00:22:40,233 --> 00:22:42,235
What did he say?

180
00:22:44,367 --> 00:22:46,404
Cat got your tongue?

181
00:22:50,567 --> 00:22:52,513
I can't digest it myself

182
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:55,581
You won't be able to bear it
You are better off not knowing

183
00:22:55,733 --> 00:22:56,905
I am better off not knowing?

184
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:58,308
What did he say?

185
00:23:00,333 --> 00:23:01,573
Where are you going?

186
00:23:01,733 --> 00:23:03,041
I want to see Victor

187
00:23:03,133 --> 00:23:04,578
Aren't you working?

188
00:23:06,433 --> 00:23:10,404
I am having a baby
I won't be working

189
00:23:10,633 --> 00:23:12,738
Now that you are here you might
as well tell me loud and clear

190
00:23:16,133 --> 00:23:19,580
I am having a baby
I won't be working

191
00:23:26,267 --> 00:23:29,476
We must deliver the chocolates in time

192
00:23:29,567 --> 00:23:32,514
Only you can do it,
we can't trust these guys

193
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,409
Be a sport

194
00:24:11,367 --> 00:24:12,641
What are you doing here?

195
00:24:14,700 --> 00:24:17,010
Murthy asked me to work

196
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:20,606
I swear on my wife
I didn't ask him to work

197
00:24:21,533 --> 00:24:24,275
He has to be in hospital
Why are you delaying him?

198
00:24:24,367 --> 00:24:28,509
I agree totally
What are you doing here?

199
00:24:28,633 --> 00:24:30,408
Krishna never lies

200
00:24:32,267 --> 00:24:34,440
Did Bhanu give you a list?

201
00:24:36,067 --> 00:24:39,139
Murthy, drop Krishna in the market
when you go for delivery

202
00:24:39,233 --> 00:24:42,442
Buy everything, go to the hospital
I'll see you later

203
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:47,076
What do you have to buy?

204
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:49,976
I 'll buy kaajal for her twinkling eyes

205
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:52,842
Tiny anklets as a tinkling device

206
00:24:52,934 --> 00:24:55,642
Oh! 1 more in my to-do list

207
00:24:55,834 --> 00:24:58,713
Why don't I remember what it is?

208
00:24:58,934 --> 00:25:01,642
A blue shirt for that pretty face

209
00:25:01,733 --> 00:25:04,441
I'll add a pink dress just in case

210
00:25:04,533 --> 00:25:07,241
Let me shop till I drop

211
00:25:07,334 --> 00:25:09,837
On a horse I'll gallop!

212
00:25:09,933 --> 00:25:13,073
All for the baby?
Nothing for Bhanu?

213
00:25:14,133 --> 00:25:15,703
Oh! You bet Bhanu will get

214
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:18,576
An apple to keep the doctor away

215
00:25:18,667 --> 00:25:21,443
Horlicks in milk everyday

216
00:25:21,534 --> 00:25:24,105
Bhanu, my love so fair

217
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:26,646
just like my baby I shall care

218
00:25:26,733 --> 00:25:29,441
Jeweled necklace like a crown

219
00:25:29,534 --> 00:25:32,310
Waist thread to show my baby has grown

220
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:35,074
1 more to tick in my dream list

221
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:38,204
Oh right here...this is it!

222
00:25:38,300 --> 00:25:41,281
- Is this also for Bhanu?
- No, for the baby

223
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:46,577
I'll soon have a baby of my own
A mini girl or boy

224
00:25:46,900 --> 00:25:52,578
She or he will ask me
to buy many a cuddly toy

225
00:25:53,567 --> 00:25:54,910
No need

226
00:26:50,733 --> 00:26:53,612
Krishna, should the baby
be like the mom or dad?

227
00:26:54,334 --> 00:26:57,076
Not a carbon copy of her dad

228
00:26:57,167 --> 00:26:59,841
...nor like his mom, for I'll be glad

229
00:26:59,933 --> 00:27:02,641
...if God decides to add
a bit of both mom and dad!!

230
00:27:02,733 --> 00:27:05,771
Baby should laugh with joy never be sad

231
00:27:09,667 --> 00:27:11,510
Is this that beautiful laughter?

232
00:27:11,834 --> 00:27:14,178
What do we get when the baby is born?

233
00:27:14,267 --> 00:27:17,111
Lots of chocolates shall be my treat

234
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:20,010
Whole of Ooty will enjoy a feast

235
00:27:20,100 --> 00:27:22,944
What else shall I add to my wish list?

236
00:27:23,067 --> 00:27:25,013
I'll think and tell you what it is

237
00:27:25,967 --> 00:27:28,208
Okay, what will you do with the baby?

238
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:31,376
I'll watch him play...with other kids

239
00:27:31,467 --> 00:27:34,141
Tease hen..mock fight with counter bids

240
00:27:34,234 --> 00:27:36,714
What else will I do...?

241
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:39,610
- What will you do?
- I'll ask Bhanu and tell you

242
00:27:40,133 --> 00:27:42,272
You won't play with Bhanu?

243
00:27:42,367 --> 00:27:45,041
Apparently I have to wait
for 300 days long

244
00:27:45,133 --> 00:27:47,773
It seems the baby
has to grow real strong

245
00:27:47,900 --> 00:27:50,710
Till then I'll Middle my thumbs and wait

246
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:55,271
So said the doctor that's my fate!

247
00:28:00,367 --> 00:28:02,278
Take this with you

248
00:28:07,867 --> 00:28:10,438
- Where are you going?
- I'm having a baby

249
00:28:55,967 --> 00:28:58,345
You've got a baby girl

250
00:29:24,534 --> 00:29:27,344
I gave your hand back to you

251
00:29:30,767 --> 00:29:32,440
I am your daddy

252
00:29:36,867 --> 00:29:43,682
Does she look like me or Bhanu?

253
00:29:47,400 --> 00:29:50,540
Where is Bhanu?

254
00:29:50,634 --> 00:29:53,774
Bhanu isn't here

255
00:29:56,500 --> 00:29:59,003
She has to nurse the baby

256
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:04,880
When will she come?
Where has she gone?

257
00:30:04,967 --> 00:30:07,607
She's with God

258
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:28,440
Take one last look

259
00:30:29,167 --> 00:30:34,167
Fair moon...silver moon
Fluffy cloud here's looking for you

260
